Text: I should be reflectivity.
I will try, but it is very difficult - describing what am I doing, similar to writing a diary, which I have never used to do it.
Some of the problems that have arisen are communication but not with the help of tools - it works quite well, but I can't express my thoughts quickly and in a proper way.
This is the most frustrating because I know exactly what I should say (in Polish: )) and how to solve the problem, but.
That is great that in our team are people who are very helpful and some of them in a similar situation, but some things take me much more time than they should have or I would like to.
There are a lot of things relating to this project I am afraid of - and it is not a new tool like for example GitHub or any other programming language.
I'm afraid we'll get stuck and focus on the insignificant aspect.
Or we will don't know what to do next.
It was this week.
After our first meeting with the client, most all of us were confused.
I supposed to, that there will be something different, then in the project brief, but some aspects were still not clear for me.
Too many thoughts, too many ideas from the client, and a lack of finding the solution.
I always try to approach the situation in this way to find a solution to the problem, not pile it up and I have the impression that this week we were spreading ourselves too thin.
The light at the end of the tunnel for me was that what Kiki said that there is the behavioral theory and she was working with such kind of project.
I started to kick deeper to know is there any tool for changing the behavior and can we use it in our project at least partially.
The article which Teacher1 sent to us was also very helpful to work out the solution.
We have finally found it - at least theoretically.
I don't know yet how it will look like in practice.
What is really important to me that we shared the tasks not only because of what someone would like to prepare but also because of the time that everyone had.
Each of us takes into account what another person in the team has to do besides the project:  exams this week, assignments, labs,Â  etc.
The main goals which were in this week were gained:  meeting with the client, find out what they would like to get from us, preparing the proposal and presentation, dividing task.
As I have already mentioned the part with dividing tasks and preparing some sections were quite clear and fast, but my impression is that I am not well prepared and have too little knowledge.
Even though I am not afraid of new things, that I would like to more focus on using some tool / RStudio/ algorithms, visualization, etc, instead of doing some behavioral research.
I have also mixed feelings about presentation.
After what I have seen on Friday I know, that our presentation wasn't enough good.
And I do not mean substantive issues, but form and shape of our presentation.
We have been focused to find the solution and to information, that for presentation is enough two slides.
Now I know, that we have to improve it for next time and always thinking who will be the audience of our presentation.
GitHub -Â  I have already handled and have checked how it works through RStudio.
Because I work with GitBucket during my INFO201, it was much easier for me than for any other team member.
It wasn't exactly the same, but I know the procedure and tools are similar.

I know that our client has CSV files and what I have heard during Project1 Team presentation there are possibilities to upload these files to RStudio and work out on them - I am really curious how it works and what we can do with such kind of files, but I am not sure if there will be a chance for doing something like this.
It is not the same as Excel that's why I am interested in it.
Thank you for remembering us that this project is also for us and the company will not bankrupt if we will not finish it.
Overall
